This is an understandable prejudice, but it is unfortunately an uninformed one since the advent of Windows XP and the continuing poor performance of MacOS. The key difference herein is that MacOS does not actually multitask (pre OSX), but engages in a furious form of toggling that, if enacted by humans, would resemble something like a drunk ninja juggling knives over a helpless baby; it may resemble something impressive, but behind the scenes, you know there's a lot of crying and wailing going on.<br>
<br>
By comparison, Windows XP, building upon the Windows NT kernel, has never been a more stable OS. In the 18 months that I've been using Windows XP on my machines, it has never once crashed (the blue screen of death is obsolescent). MacOS continually has its crashing (e.g., &quot;Finder has stopped responding&quot;, or &quot;Chooser cannot start&quot;). <br>
<br>
